description._content: Catalog #: 09_01771 Title: Frederick A. Hoover Special Collection Photo Additional Information: Navy guests with Capt. K. E. Taylor, C.O. (center second row) and Cdr W. E. Lamb (kneeling left) on the flight deck of USS Shangri-La CVA-38. In the background is an F8U-1 Crusader, Frederick A. Hoover was the 100th individual to receive his aviator license (June 8th 1912). He performed stunts in air shows and was known as 'The Death Cheating Aviator"". He was a member of the Early Birds of Aviation. Corporation Name: Vought Tags: Frederick A.
